29
00:01:44,880 --> 00:01:49,480
That's more than three times the amount recommended by the WHO.

30
00:01:49,480 --> 00:01:56,120
Here, Marion explains some of the reasons behind this to BBC World Service programme, the Food Chain.

31
00:01:56,120 --> 00:02:03,960
We consume lots of salt, which is due to historical heritage, because when we were normal

32
00:02:03,960 --> 00:02:10,080
for centuries and centuries, we travelled and wandered across the steps.

33
00:02:10,080 --> 00:02:17,599
And here we had to carry lots of meat, which could be preserved only adding salt.

34
00:02:17,599 --> 00:02:24,920
And even the milk products, the dairy products are also very much salty for the same reasons.

35
00:02:24,919 --> 00:02:30,159
Besides improving its flavour, salt can be used to preserve food, to stop it from going

36
00:02:30,159 --> 00:02:31,159
bad.

37
00:02:31,159 --> 00:02:34,399
Traditionally, people in Kazakhstan were nomads.

38
00:02:34,399 --> 00:02:38,959
They travelled from place to place with their animals, rather than living in one place

39
00:02:38,959 --> 00:02:40,560
